post_text:
Dear David Ellis West Parents and Caregivers,

We wanted to start by thanking you all as parents and caregivers for your fantastic support and patience. We are particularly appreciative of everything that you have been doing to support learning from home. We know how difficult it is to juggle working and supporting your own children with their online schooling, and this is of course in addition to dealing with all of the normal challenges of family life. We've received a number of messages of thanks and support from so many of you over these past few weeks, and these are all received very gratefully indeed. Thank you.

Please do remember to contact us if you need any support. In the meantime, we send our very best wishes to you and your families for a safe and successful school year.

Yours sincerely,

Maria Green
Tyron D. Hurd
Marcy Novak
Sharisse Spencer
Kimberleyn Williams

post_text:
David Ellis Academy West will be using a COVID-19 daily screening mobile app this school year called Fever Free. The app will monitor temperature and symptom checks. The app will allow them to do a privately recorded video temperature check of the child(ren) and symptom check prior to coming to school. If the child(ren) is fever and symptom-free, the app will show a ‚Äúcleared for arrival‚Äù badge. This badge must be shown upon arrival at the school in order for the student to gain access to the building. If the child(ren) is not fever or symptom-free, the app will notify the parent that the child(ren) must remain home and give them further instructions.

In order to use the app, the parent must have a digital thermometer.

If 1 child is cleared for arrival, but one of the siblings is not, all of the children in that household must remain home and not report to the school. Further instructions will be given at that time.

The link below is a brief video you can show if you wish of how this easy user-friendly app works.

https://youtu.be/MGWD8L87Q5M

Return to Learn Zoom Meeting for Parents
Hello Parents,

As promised, we will be hosting parent meetings via Zoom to share information about the school‚Äôs learning models and action plans. The first Zoom meeting is scheduled for Thursday, August 6, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Online Learners only). The second Zoom meeting is scheduled for Friday, August 7, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Hybrid/In-Person Learners only).

There is no need to attend both of these Zoom Meetings days, as they will have different information specific to each learning model. We wanted to give a couple of different times that will work around your busy schedules. The information to access the Zoom meeting was sent to parents via email. Thank you for your participation and support. Stay safe and healthy!

Sincerely,

The David Ellis West Leadership Team

Zoom Meeting Schedule

Days/Times:
*Thurs., August 6, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Online Learners only).
*Fri., August 7, 2020, at 11:00 am and 3:00 pm (Hybrid/In-Person Learners only).

NO SCHOOL FOR STUDENTS - MARCH 13-APRIL 5, 2020

Good Morning DEAW Families,

Governor Whitmer announced the statewide closure of all K-12 school buildings from March 16 through April 5, 2020.

In addition, David Ellis Academy West will be closed today Friday, March 13 for students. Google Classroom will be an instrumental part of the online learning environment during the closure period. Therefore, staff members will be reporting to receive additional Google Classroom training.

Parents/Students are asked to visit the school today Friday, March 13, 2020 between 9:00-11:00 a.m. or 1:00-3:00 p.m. to pick up their belongings and to receive other important information.
We understand that this may be an inconvenience to some, so we apologize for the late notice.

Thank you for your understanding.

post_text:
After-school Programing Canceled!

Dear David Ellis Academy West Families,

Please be advised that effective immediately the decision has been made to cancel all after-school activities including tutoring, STEM, robotics, choir, etc. and non-essential gatherings (field trips, Wax Museum, The Lion King play, basketball and volleyball games, etc.). We will continue to offer morning and afternoon KidZone service until further notice. Parents are asked to make the necessary arrangements to ensure their children are picked up on time at dismissal.

Thank you for your individual efforts to keep our students, staff, and your families safe. Moving forward our school will make determinations foremost on the safety and well-being of students, staff and our entire school community, and with the input of local and state officials. We thank you for your continued support and partnership as we address this situation together.

Best regards,

The David Ellis Academy West Leadership Team

Dear Parents,

Due to the winter weather advisory, the decision has been made to close school tomorrow Wednesday, February 26, 2020.

We do not take the decision to close school lightly. We value learning and recognize the impact that canceling school has on our students and families. The safety and wellbeing of our students, staff, and families are paramount in any decision to close the school.

Heavy snowfall and slippery roads will make for dangerous and unsafe travel conditions for our students and families.

Students are expected to log into their iReady and Kahn Academy accounts as well as complete work on their Science fair projects.

Be safe and have a good evening.

Sincerely,

Tyron D. Hurd

post_text: DEAW's 5th grade jumped into the world of art, design, and electrical engineering today! They made simply beautiful Christmas Card Paper Circuits! A paper circuit is a low-voltage electronic circuit that is created on paper or cardboard using conductive copper tape, LEDs and a power source such as a coin-cell battery. Creating paper circuits is a good way to teach the basics of electricity and how circuits function. Through the Science, Math, & Artistic process they had to troubleshoot, investigate, practice patience, focus on the task, and use complex thinking! They were allowed to be creative & even listened to a little holiday music while they worked! Such a fun & festive day! Happy Holiday's! #STEMintegration #STEM #futureengineers Jessica James Amanda Ash Richard Rainville & Derek Zuidema

post_text: Our 2nd graders worked on their place value skills. They used hands-on math manipulatives to build Base 10 Towers. Our DIY Place Value Cup Activity cemented expanded form concepts. They also started to work with money and practice math on the Chromebooks via Khan Academy. Great job 2nd grade!! Jessica James, Brittney Urban, Ryan Molnar & Katelyn Tucco.

post_text:
It's National Coding Week! Thank you @amazon for lending us 10 of your awesome engineers today! They shared their academic journey and exposed our 3rd, 4th, & 5th graders to new ideas, new career options, and hosted an Hour of Code in each class!

The students LOVED coding and worked so well with the Software Engineers! They asked great questions, recieved certificates, and a few future scholars recieved trivia question gifts!

A huge thanks to our STEM Coordinator, Jessica James!!
